libbdplus
------------------------------------------
This library is written for the purpose of playing Blu-ray movies. It is
intended for software that want to support Blu-ray playback (such as VLC and
MPlayer). We, the authors of this library, do not condone nor endorse piracy.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.8.1-1
  libbdplus-devel-0.1.2-1bl2
  libbdplus0-0.1.2-1bl2
  libgcrypt20-1.7.6-1
  libgpg-error0-1.27-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.videolan.org/developers/libbdplus.html

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.videolan.org/pub/videolan/libbdplus/0.1.2/libbdplus-0.1.2.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbdplus-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbdplus-0.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbdplus-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus0-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus-devel-0.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbdplus)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbdplus.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/README.txt

(libbdplus0)
  /usr/bin/cygbdplus-0.dll

(libbdplus-devel)
  /usr/include/libbdplus/bdplus-version.h
  /usr/include/libbdplus/bdplus.h
  /usr/lib/libbdplus.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libbdplus.pc

------------------

